summary:
My name is Maria Lecheva, I live in Netherland, for now in Assen. I am 26 years old from Varna, Bulgaria. 
I have studied dental medicine at the "Medical University of Varna" for 6 years Master’s Degree
program. The Medical university is the best ranked university in Bulgaria and has the biggest of three
dental faculties in the country. The program provided 3 years of general medicine studying and 3 years
dental practice with patients on fully equipped dental units.
Every summer we had obligatory dental practice as dental assistants and I have worked for three
different clinics. I managed to get acquainted with the approaches of the dentists for managing cases
and treatment planning. After I graduated I started working as a general dentist as a full-time job in the
city of Devnya. In the clinic I had all kinds of cases for conservative, endodontic, non-fixed and fixed
prosthetic, periodontal treatment and extractions. In a smaller city I have a greater number of patients
which leads to expectation of a big variety of individual care for each of them.
The proper working relations and working conditions have a big role in providing quality in treatment. I think that pleasing the patient's needs and requirements should be the goal of every successful dentist. So I am concentrated in finding good colleagues, working atmosphere and patient satisfaction. I am very self - critical and strict in connection to the working process which has been noted from the patients. I am very
eager for new challenges and I have always appreciated and valued every lecture, course or symposium
for professional development and qualification.
